data.title: Hey Cinderella
data.text:
"Hey Cinderella" is a song co-written and recorded by American country music artist Suzy Bogguss. It was released in November 1993 as the second single from her album Something Up My Sleeve. The song reached number 5 on the Billboard Hot Country Singles & Tracks chart in February 1994.[1] The single also entered the UK singles chart, reaching number 92 on September 25, 1993. It was written by Bogguss, Matraca Berg and Gary Harrison.

For the Muppets television special, see Hey, Cinderella!
